  "why": "The paper applies mutations mainly in continuous intermediate (latent) spaces via generative models (GANs) and does not describe enforcing serialized input format constraints (e.g., clipping/rounding to integer [0,255] pixel values or saving images into standard formats). The core transformation mechanism is G(z+v) on latent vectors and the paper explicitly describes Jacobian/latent-vector based edits (Section 4.1/4.2) and using BigGAN/StyleGAN to prepare latent vectors (Section 6). While the authors validate the perceptual validity of generated images via human studies, they do not discuss serialization, integer clipping, or any steps to ensure that fault-inducing perturbations survive conversion to standard image file formats. Because mutations are performed in continuous/latent representations without any stated enforcement of storage-format constraints, the failure-reproducibility concern described in the metric applies and thus the appropriate rating is Low.",
